  "steps": [
    "Start with 975 mL, water",
    "3.0 g NaCl",
    "2.5 g Peptone",
    "17 g Agar",
    "Autoclave with stir bar",
    "Cool to 55 °C (faster in water bath)",
    "Then add the following while stirring on heat plate (DO NOT OVERHEAT)",
    "0.5 mL of 1 Molarity (M) CaCl2 (sterile)",
    "1 mL of 5 mg/mL Cholesterol (dissolved in ethanol)",
    "1 mL of 1 Molarity (M) MgSO4 (sterile)",
    "25 mL of 1 Molarity (M) Potassium Phosphate Buffer, pH 6.0 (sterile)",
    "Pour into petri dishes using sterile technique 60 mm dishes = About 7 mL per plate 100 mm dishes = About 20 mL per plate"
  ],
